						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Māsti-stone set up in the open site of Hirē-matha.</hi></p>						

						<p>13th-14th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record states that the <hi rend="italic">bīra-gallu</hi> for Channappa and the <hi rend="italic">māstikallu</hi> for his wife Nāgaundi were installed. It is in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">13th-14th Century A.D.</hi> </p>						

